 handle to the file or I/O device (for example, a file, file stream, physical disk, volume, console buffer, tape drive, socket, communications resource, mailslot, or pipe).

The hFile parameter must have been created with the write access. For more information, see Generic Access Rights and File Security and Access Rights.

